window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Lovelace was once merely a ship's artificial intelligence. When she wakes up in a new body following a total system shutdown and reboot, she has to start over in a synthetic body, in a world where her kind are illegal. She's never felt so alone. But she's not alone, not really. </p> <p>Pepper, one of the engineers who risked life and limb to reinstall Lovelace, is determined to help her adjust to her new world. Because Pepper knows a thing or two about starting over. </p> <p>Together Pepper and Lovey will discover that, huge as the galaxy may be, it's anything but empty. <i>The Long Way to a Small, Angry Planet</i> introduced listeners to the incredible imagination of Becky Chambers and has been nominated for any number of awards and accolades, including the Baileys Prize for Women's Fiction, the Tiptree Award, the Kitschies Golden Tentacle and the Arthur C. Clarke Award. </p> <p><i>A Closed and Common Orbit</i> is the stand-alone sequel to <i>The Long Way to a Small, Angry Planet</i> and is perfect for fans of <i>Firefly</i>, Joss Whedon, <i>Mass Effect</i> and Star Wars. </p>"; 
